  The simplest path:                                                                                                                    
   
  1. Create an AppDir structure manually:                                                                                               
  AppDir/                                                   
    AppRun          ← shell script that launches the app                                                                                
    app.desktop     ← required by AppImage spec         
    app.png         ← icon                                                                                                              
    usr/                                                                                                                                
      bin/python3   ← symlink or copy from venv                                                                                         
      lib/python3.x/site-packages/  ← copied from venv                                                                                  
    app/            ← your source code copied here                                                                                      
                                                            
  2. AppRun is just:                                                                                                                    
  #!/bin/bash                                                                                                                           
  APPDIR="$(dirname "$(readlink -f "$0")")"                                                                                             
  exec "$APPDIR/usr/bin/python3" "$APPDIR/app/main.py" "$@"                                                                             
                                                                                                                                        
  3. Package it:                                                                                                                        
  appimagetool AppDir/ TopDogSpectrumAnalyser-x86_64.AppImage                                                                           
                                                                                                                                        
  That's it. appimagetool is a single downloaded binary, no complex recipe needed.                                                      
                                                                                                                                        
  The one step that requires a bit of care is making sure the venv's Python and site-packages are self-contained (no hardcoded absolute 
  paths pointing back to /home/spicy/...). PyQt6 installed via pip into a venv is generally fine for this — it ships its own Qt6        
  libraries inside the wheel so there are no system Qt6 dependencies to worry about. You can verify with ldd on the .so files in the    
  venv if anything looks suspicious.                        

  Your compiled hackrf_sweep_iq binary can just go into AppDir/usr/bin/ and will be on PATH when the AppRun script runs.  
